direct_answer.text:
To clarify,

First, find out how many windows are left:

\[ \text{Total Windows} - \text{Installed Windows} = \text{Windows Left} \]

\[ 9 - 6 = 3 \]

So, there are 3 windows left to be installed.

Given that it takes 6 hours to install each window, calculate the total time taken to install the remaining windows:

\[ \text{Time per Window} \times \text{Windows Left} = \text{Total Time} \]

\[ 6 \times 3 = 18 \]

Therefore, it will take 18 hours to install the rest of the windows.

The answer is: **18 hours**.
